# Ambiguous Masyu Builder

Place five copies of each of the five 3x3 tiles from the right of the grid into the grid (without rotation or reflection) such that each tile shows up exactly once in each row and each column, then solve as an Ambiguous Masyu.

Click the image to solve on Penpa+.
